1. Load the workbook.
2. Gather all IDs present in Foglio1 column E.
3. Scan DATI rows, keep those whose ID (col K) is in the Foglio1 ID set, preserving order.
4. Take the last 10 of those matching rows.
5. Copy columns G‑P (7‑16) from each selected DATI row into Foglio1 rows 2‑11 (the first 10 data rows) in the same columns G‑P.
6. Save the modified workbook to the output directory, recalculate formulas, and verify that the target cells now contain values.
